arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: This collection is organized into one series.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains annual issues of Jackson College Handbook between 1911 and 1970. It is an annual booklet containing rules, regulations, and information for students of Jackson College.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office of Publications is one of four departments comprising Tufts Office of Communications. This Office is responsible producing magazines, newsletters, and marketing material for Tufts University. Through design and writing the Office of Publication aims to capture and share the visual and intellectual identity of the University. The Office also offers editorial, design, and project management services for Tufts departments, and maintains external contracts with photographers and design firms.

processinfo.head: Processing status
processinfo.p: This collection is processed and open for research
